  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Reality Composer provides many actions that you can use as building blocks when constructing",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a behavior’s action sequence. Common actions include moving objects in your scene,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "animating objects in a variety of ways, playing sounds, adding force to objects that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "participate in the physics simulation, and transitioning to a completely different",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "scene. You can also call functions written in Xcode to accomplish additional tasks",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "beyond what the built-in actions can do.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Move-rotate-or-scale-an-object-from-a-behavior",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Move, rotate, or scale an object from a behavior",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Behaviors can transform objects to a specific location, rotation, and scale using",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the Move, Rotate, Scale To action, which animates objects smoothly to a specified",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "world position, orientation, and size. The end result of using a Move, Rotate, Scale",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "To action is the same regardless of its targets’ starting transform values. For example,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "if you create a behavior with a Move, Rotate, Scale To action configured with a scale",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "value of 0.5, all of its targeted objects end up with a scale value of 0.5, regardless",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of what their starting scale value was.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-interactivity-to-behaviors-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Behaviors can also transform objects relative to their starting position, orientation,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and size using the Move, Rotate, Scale By action. With this action, the values you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "enter into the transform fields are applied to the objects’ current transform values",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "instead of being used as absolute values. As a result, a Move, Rotate, Scale By action",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "has a different effect when run against objects with different starting transform",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "values. The action’s position and rotation values are added to an object’s starting",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "position and rotation values, while its scale value is multiplied by the object’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "starting scale value.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For example, a Move, Rotate, Scale By action with a Location X value of 5 cm results",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in each of its target objects moving 5 centimeters from its starting position along",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the scene’s X-axis. Similarly, configuring a Move, Rotate, Scale By action with a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "scale value of 0.5, and running it against an object with a starting scale value",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of 10.0, results in an object with a scale value of 5.0 when the action finishes.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "That same action run against an object with a starting scale value of 2.0, however,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "results in an object with a scale value of 1.0 after the behavior runs.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-interactivity-to-behaviors-2",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "With both of these actions, you can enter the move, rotate, or scale amount into",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the action’s text fields, or use the manipulator to make the transform changes visually",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in the scene. With the Behaviors pane visible and a behavior selected, clicking or",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "tapping a Move, Rotate, Scale By or Move, Rotate, Scale To action puts the scene",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "into interactive mode, as shown in the following figure. Interactive mode lets you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "use the manipulator to transform the object to the desired location, orientation,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and scale. While in interactive mode, the scene view shows both the starting and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "ending location, orientation, and scale.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-interactivity-to-behaviors-3",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Draw-attention-to-an-object",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Draw attention to an object",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To draw attention to an object, use the Emphasize action, which causes one or more",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "objects in your scene to animate in place in a variety of ways, such as shaking,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "flipping, jiggling, spinning, or bouncing.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Add-force-to-an-object",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Add force to an object",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Behaviors can add forces to any object in your scene that participates in the physics",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "simulation, by using the Add Force action to simulate the effects of being pushed,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "kicked, tossed, or blown by wind. Once you’ve selected the object or objects that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the force applies to, a manipulator that represents the direction and intensity of",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the force to be added appears in your scene. To change the direction of the force,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "move the blue cone or rotate the blue ring. To change the amount of force to apply,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "use the Velocity slider on the action.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-interactivity-to-behaviors-4",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Play-sounds-from-a-behavior",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Play sounds from a behavior",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "There are three actions that play audio files in Reality Composer scenes: Play Sound,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Play Ambience, and Play Music. All three actions function similarly, but are designed",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for slightly different purposes:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "text": "Play Sound",
                          "type": "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type": "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " action plays a sound as if it were coming from a specific object",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "in your scene. The volume of the sound changes based on the camera position relative",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "to the object, and whether the camera is pointed toward or away from it. When the",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "user is near the object, the sound plays louder, and when the user is far from the",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "object, the sound is softer.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "text": "Play Ambience",
                          "type": "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type": "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " action plays sounds anchored to your scene. These sounds track",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "change in orientation but don’t attenuate, so the volume of an ambient sound doesn’t",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "change based on the user’s position relative to any object in the scene. Play Ambience",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "actions are designed for playing background noise that sounds as if it’s coming from",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "far away.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "text": "Play Music",
                          "type": "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type": "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " action plays sounds at a constant volume, completely independent",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "of the user’s position and orientation, and is designed for playing background music",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "and voice narration.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Transition-to-another-scene",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Transition to another scene",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For games and complex AR experiences, you might choose to split up your app’s content",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "into multiple scenes to keep things better organized and to reduce load time and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the amount of memory required. You might, for example, choose to have a separate",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "scene for every level in a game.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To switch to a different scene, use a Change Scene action, specifying the new scene",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you wish to load. To reset the current scene to its starting state, select the current",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "scene instead of a different scene.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Call-code-from-a-behavior",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Call code from a behavior",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To call code you’ve written in Xcode from a behavior, use the Notify action. Notify",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "actions have a single configurable parameter called Identifier that is used to uniquely",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "identify the notification this action sends. By default, a Notify action’s identifier",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is the same as the behavior name, but you can change it to any string value that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "makes sense for your project. Xcode’s code generation uses the identifier value to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "automatically create a notification that you use to respond to this action.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "adding-interactivity-to-behaviors-5",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To write code that responds to a Notify action, first write a code function that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "takes an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/Entity",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter. This function should contain the code that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you want your behavior to call:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "    func handleTapOnEntity(_ entity: Entity?) {",
            "        guard let entity = entity else { return }        ",
            "        // Do something with entity...",
            "    }"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Once you have your function, you register it as the action’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "onAction",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " handler.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Because the Notify action in the preceding figure specifies an identifier value of",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Tapped",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", Xcode automatically creates an action called ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "tapped",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " on the class representing",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "its scene. Assign the new function as the generated action’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "onAction",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " handler to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "call that function whenever the behavior is triggered.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "    // Register an onAction handler for the notification",
            "    // action you created in Reality Composer",
            "    boxAnchor.actions.tapped.onAction = handleTapOnEntity(_:)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
